genresAdvancedInfo.name: australian blues
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Australian blues is a genre of music that has its roots in African American culture but has been adapted and developed in Australia. It is characterized by its soulful and emotive sound, often featuring slow tempos, bluesy guitar riffs, and powerful vocals. Australian blues artists often draw inspiration from the Australian landscape and culture, incorporating elements of folk and country music into their sound.
